        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1855755415" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14647693709014645556">3.5 Stars<br/><br/>In the Goodreads’ description of this book they use the word &quot;dazzling,&quot; by no means was I &quot;dazzled&quot; by this story, but I was entertained. Brit Bennett has created a story full of lies, deep sadness and lifelong regrets which become heavy burdens for some of the characters. The book mainly focuses on three main characters ranging in age from the late teens to early twenties, which gave me the feeling, at times, that I was reading a YA novel. Don&apos;t get me wrong, there is some heavy plot </span>
  <span id="freeText14647693709014645556" style="display:none">3.5 Stars<br /><br />In the Goodreads’ description of this book they use the word "dazzling," by no means was I "dazzled" by this story, but I was entertained. Brit Bennett has created a story full of lies, deep sadness and lifelong regrets which become heavy burdens for some of the characters. The book mainly focuses on three main characters ranging in age from the late teens to early twenties, which gave me the feeling, at times, that I was reading a YA novel. Don't get me wrong, there is some heavy plot lines here, such as suicide and abortion, but the ages of the characters and some of the scenarios in the story kept throwing me off. <br /><br />This wasn't so much a memorable story for me, as it was a memorable debut from an author who clearly has talent.<br /> <br /></span>
