<div id="review_1776099238" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1776099238" />
    <a title="Ify" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5587447-ify"><img alt="Ify" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1611337881p2/5587447.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1776099238?book_show_action=true">Oct 16, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ify" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ify" href="/user/show/5587447-ify">Ify</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1776099238" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1143714918740023913">Y&apos;all I&apos;m conflicted... I really liked this novel- the writing, the overall plot and its lack of a clear-cut ending. At one point, I couldn&apos;t even put the book down. But, I felt somewhat disappointed by the predictable path this novel took. There were a couple melodramatic scenes that were Tyler Perry-esque, that had me clutching my imaginary pearls or groaning in dismay. I just felt like the author could have taken this plot somewhere unexpected &amp; killed it. <br/><br/>Why do I feel conflicted? Because al</span>
  <span id="freeText1143714918740023913" style="display:none">Y'all I'm conflicted... I really liked this novel- the writing, the overall plot and its lack of a clear-cut ending. At one point, I couldn't even put the book down. But, I felt somewhat disappointed by the predictable path this novel took. There were a couple melodramatic scenes that were Tyler Perry-esque, that had me clutching my imaginary pearls or groaning in dismay. I just felt like the author could have taken this plot somewhere unexpected &amp; killed it. <br /><br />Why do I feel conflicted? Because although the main thread of the plot took a predictable route, it was written so well, took on a few heavy social (&amp; religious) issues and it ended w/o a clear resolution. <br /><br />Solid 4 stars. </span>
  <a data-text-id="1143714918740023913" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


